Overview
========

.. code:: console

   $ unihist2 --help
   usage: unihist2 [-h] [--version] [-G] [FILE ...]

   positional arguments:
     FILE        file to analyze (default: stdin)

   options:
     -h, --help  show this help message and exit
     --version   show version information and exit
     -G          use Extended Grapheme Clusters

   $ unihist2 /path/to/unihist2/LICENSE
   19              U+000A  LINE FEED
   152             U+0020  SPACE
   1       (       U+0028  LEFT PARENTHESIS
   1       )       U+0029  RIGHT PARENTHESIS
   22      ,       U+002C  COMMA
   ⋮
   12      w       U+0077  LATIN SMALL LETTER W
   7       y       U+0079  LATIN SMALL LETTER Y
   1       ©       U+00A9  COPYRIGHT SIGN
   2       “       U+201C  LEFT DOUBLE QUOTATION MARK
   2       ”       U+201D  RIGHT DOUBLE QUOTATION MARK

Prerequisites
=============

* Python ≥ 3.7

* regex_ (for the -G option)

.. _regex:
   https://pypi.org/project/regex/

* unicodedata2_ (optional)

.. _unicodedata2:
   https://pypi.org/project/unicodedata2/

